<item>
            <title>[HIVE-937] CONCAT UDF for GROUP BY</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-937</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be nice to have a UDF like CONCAT for GROUP BY.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SELECT user, CONCAT(post) AS posts&lt;br/&gt;
FROM tablename&lt;br/&gt;
GROUP BY user&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...which would return all of the posts concatenated together, separated by a single whitespace. So if the table was like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;user\tpost&lt;br/&gt;
1\tHi there this is my first post&lt;br/&gt;
1\tpost number two&lt;br/&gt;
2\tI&apos;m a different user!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;then the above code would return&lt;br/&gt;
user\tposts&lt;br/&gt;
1\tHi there this is my first post post number two&lt;br/&gt;
2\tI&apos;m a different user!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternate form:&lt;br/&gt;
CONCAT(string text, string separator) which would put the separator between each block of text.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
